# DeadMile AI — Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
DeadMile AI is an enterprise AI platform that helps small trucking carriers (3-10 trucks) maximize profitability by eliminating dead miles. An AI agent analyzes loads, calculates TRUE net profitability, factors in destination market quality, and recommends optimal loads including multi-hop chains.

## Architecture: 7 Microservices + Infrastructure
- **api-gateway** — FastAPI + Pydantic v2, REST API routing to internal services
- **agent-core** — LangGraph agent with 8 tools, SSE streaming
- **load-ingestion** — Parses 3 text formats + PDF broker sheets, publishes to Kafka
- **load-processor** — Kafka consumer, geocoding enrichment, Postgres storage
- **profitability-engine** — Net profit: revenue - fuel - driver_pay - insurance - maintenance - tolls - deadhead
- **market-intelligence** — Market scoring, XGBoost rate prediction, K-Means clustering
- **frontend** — Next.js 15 App Router, Tailwind, shadcn/ui, Deck.gl maps

## Data Stores
- PostgreSQL 16 + PostGIS + TimescaleDB
- Qdrant (vector search), Redis (caching), MinIO (PDF storage)

## Event Streaming
- Apache Kafka + Zookeeper (load ingestion pipeline)
- Temporal (multi-hop load chain orchestration)

## AI/ML Stack
- LangGraph, LiteLLM → OpenAI GPT-4o-mini (Groq/Featherless/Ollama via LLM_API_BASE)
- Tavily (fuel prices), Langfuse (observability), Mem0 (driver memory)
- XGBoost (rate prediction), scikit-learn K-Means (market clustering)

## Agent Tools (8)
search_loads, calculate_profitability, get_market_score, predict_lane_rate, find_load_chain, get_fuel_prices, semantic_load_search, get_driver_preferences

## Coding Standards
- Python 3.12, FastAPI 0.115+, Pydantic v2, type hints everywhere
- Next.js 15 App Router, TypeScript 5, strict mode
- Async I/O for all service-to-service calls
- Environment variables via .env (never hardcode secrets)
- Docker Compose for local dev (19 containers on deadmile-network)
- Use PostGIS GEOGRAPHY(POINT, 4326) for all spatial data
- Profitability must always be NET (all cost components included)

## Load Data Formats
- Format 1 (verbose): LOAD L-XXXXXXX with labeled fields
- Format 2 (reference): === Load Ref L-XXXXXXX === with PU/DEL lines
- Format 3 (compact): L-XXXXXXX | City,ST -> City,ST single-line
- PDF: broker_load_sheet_XXX.pdf tabular columns

## Equipment Types
Dry Van | Flatbed | Reefer | Step Deck

## Requirements
None | Hazmat | Team | Liftgate
